A BILL FOR AN ACT
RELATING TO ORGANIC WASTE.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. The legislature finds that although the State
2 did not reach mandates established in 1991 under section 342G-3,
3 Hawaii Revised Statutes, to reduce the solid waste stream by
4 fifty per cent by 2000, the aioha+ challenge established a goal
5 to reduce the solid waste stream prior to disposal by seventy
6 per cent by 2030 through source reduction, recycling,
7 bioconversion, and landfill diversion methods for organic waste.
8 The legislature further finds that county integrated solid
9 waste management plans must be submitted to the department of
10 health every ten years pursuant to section 342G-24, Hawaii
11 Revised Statutes.
12 Accordingly, the purpose of this Act is to meet United
13 Nations Sustainable Development and aloha+ challenge goals
14 related to waste reduction by embedding similar goals into the
15 integrated solid waste management plan components for the
16 counties to assess and identify benchmarks to reduce solid waste
17 production and increase organic waste diversion, while
