3 SECTION 3. Section 342G-26, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
4 amended by amending subsection (c) to read as follows:
5 "(c) The recycling bioconversion, and organic waste
6 diversion component shall identify and assess:
7 (1) The level of waste reduction the county is achieving
8 through existing recycling and bioconversion efforts;
9 (2) The type and amount of solid waste that it is
10 technically and economically feasible to recycle or
11 alter through bioconversion; [aed]
12 (3) Methods to increase and improve [tfee] recycling and
13 bioconversion efforts, including opportunities for
14 backyard composting[—]; and
15 (4) Methods to achieve organic waste stream reduction
16 goals pursuant to section 342G-3(b); provided that the
17 methods shall account for reducing potential risk of
18 transporting invasive species in organic waste.
19 For the purposes of this paragraph, "organic waste"
20 means any material that is compostable, does not
21 contain contaminants detrimental to human health and
