1 the environment, and is derived from either a plant or
2 an animal, and includes green waste, food waste,
3 food-soiled paper that is acceptable for food storage,
4 and untreated and unpainted wood waste.
5 For recycling, the counties shall assess the type and
6 amount of solid waste that it is technically feasible to
7 recycle, giving consideration at a minimum to clear glass,
8 colored glass, aluminum, steel and bimetallic cans, high-grade
9 office paper, newsprint, mixed paper, corrugated paper, HOPE,
10 PET, and green waste.
11 For bioconversion, the counties shall assess the type and
12 amount of solid waste that it is technically feasible to alter
13 through bioconversion, giving consideration at a minimum to
14 green waste, wood waste, animal manure, sewage sludge, and food
15 wastes."
16 SECTION 4. Statutory material to be repealed is bracketed
17 and stricken. New statutory material is underscored.
18 SECTION 5. This Act shall take effect on July 1, 2026.
